# Toolkit skills index

Cursor discovers skills in **this project’s** `.cursor/skills/` (each skill is a folder with `SKILL.md`). When a task matches a row below, **read that skill once** and apply it. You do not need to quote paths in the reply.

## Core engineering

| Use when… | Skill folder |
|-----------|----------------|
| Debugging, flaky tests, unclear root cause | `systematic-debug` |
| Unfamiliar area: map entry points and callers before editing | `pre-edit-context` |
| “How does X work?” — explain subsystem/flow; optional architecture critique | `how` |
| Harsh maintainability / code-judo review on a branch diff | `thermo-nuclear-code-quality-review` |
| Distinctive UI (pages, components, apps) — non-generic design | `frontend-design` |
| Live Chrome UI proof via DevTools MCP (existing profile) | `browser-use` |
| Package repeated workflows into skills/subagents | `auto-improve` |
| After non-trivial edits: run narrow tests or lint | `verify-after-change` |
| Refactor without behavior change | `safe-refactor` |
| PR / diff review before merge | `code-review-pass` |
| Package or runtime upgrades | `dependency-update` |
| Saving state for another session or person | `session-handoff` |
| HTTP/JSON API shape, errors, versioning | `api-design-basics` |
| Quiz / interview prep on this codebase | `grill-me` |
| Product requirements document | `write-a-prd` |
| Red–green–refactor workflow | `tdd` |
| Architectural improvement opportunities | `improve-codebase-architecture` |

